{
  "texts": [
    "Management theorizing often oscillates between induction, which generalizes from observations, and deduction, which develops theories from first principles (Makadok et al., 2018; Choudhury et al., 2021; Davis et al., 2007; Harrison et al., 2007; Shrestha et al., 2021).",
    "The observations derived from GABE do not neatly fit into either category.",
    "As the product of simulations, they do not constitute \"ground truth\" evidence from which inductive generalizations can be made.",
    "At the same time, they do not provide evidence external to the generating model that can be used to test its predictions.",
    "Instead, we suggest these experiments largely facilitate abductive theorizing."
  ]
}